      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GILES (1) won this trip and then delivered again over 1605m this grade. Switching back in trip shouldn't bother, but he draws out today and will need some luck in the run. Rates to go close regardless. BLUE LUPIN (2) was back to his best winning his Maiden easily this track/trip. Had an outside gate and finished hard from the back. Will have to do it the hard way again, but keeps Faithful and looks capable of taking the next step. CALEB (6) can go better back to this trip. He has pieces of form good enough and maps well. Won his Maiden four back this track/trip from the 13 gate. Consider. DREAM ILLUSION (3) will be fitter and drawn low won't be far away.",
